Im pretty sure i have good eyesight so i might be quite alone, but i felt like the jump from 1440p-4k was the same as 4k-8k. Just the starting point was so much better from 4k-8k but there was still a big difference in amount of detail.

Hey Marques! Random person on the internet here üëã I heard you mention HDR and wanted to throw in my two cents. Typically when you do HDR versus SDR, there's also an added issue of colorspace on top of white points. The reason why an HDR image may look worse when viewed on an SDR compatible device/screen is because there hasn't been a white shift/additional grade done in post (i.e. a colorist going in and tweaking the image) to accommodate the new white values, so your picture will end up looking super washed out. It's a super interesting topic, would love to hear other people's input on this!

Also for context, I'm a compositor/editor who works in the VFX industry üòä
